Package com.sri.ai.util.collect

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ArraySet<E>
    A Set interface enriched with random access methods and a list iterator.
    LazyIterator<T>
    A lazy iterator that has the capacity to iterate over its range but only compute the actual values when required.
    RandomAccessTree
    An interface for a tree, with inclusion and retrieval of valid paths.
    RandomAccessTree.GetResult
    An interface for the results of method RandomAccessTree.get(Iterator).
    StackedMap<K,V>
    A Map based on another Map (the base), and storing only the differences between itself and the base.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractStackedMap<K,V>
    A partial implementation of StackedMap.
    ArrayHashSet<E>
    Analogous to LinkedHashSet, but with an ArrayList instead of a LinkedList, offering the same advantages (random access) and disadvantages (slower addition and removal of elements), but with the extra advantage of offering an iterator that is actually a ListIterator.
    BackListIterator<E>
    A list iterator based on another list iterator reversing its direction.
    BreadthFirstIterator<T>
    An iterator based on an array of sub-iterators that ranges over all i-th elements of each sub-iterator before ranging over the (i+1)-th elements.
    CartesianProductEnumeration<E>
    A utility class for enumerating over the cartesian product of lists of lists of elements.
    CartesianProductInMapIterator<K,V>
    A iterator over the Cartesian product of the ranges of a map of iterators, indexed by an arbitrary type K.
    CartesianProductIterator<E>
    A iterator over the Cartesian product of the ranges of a list of iterators.
    CharactersAsStringsIterator
    An iterator over the characters of a given string.
    CloneableFunctionIterator<F,T>
    An extension of FunctionIterator implementing CloneableIterator.
    CopyOnWriteArraySet<E>
    A specialization of CopyOnWriteCollection for ArraySet.
    CopyOnWriteCollection<E,B extends java.util.Collection<E>>
    A Collection implementation meant to behave as a copy of a given base B, which must be a Collection type.
    CopyOnWriteMap<K,V>
    A Map implementation that directs methods to another map, which is either a map received at construction, or a copy of it to a new HashMap made upon the first writing (or potentially writing} operation.
    DefaultComparator<E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>>
    A default comparator using the Comparable.compareTo(Object) method of Comparable objects.
    DepthFirstIterator<E>
    A facility for creating a depth-first iterator over the subtrees of a user-defined tree (by default including the root subtree itself, which is the same as the original tree).
    DisjointSets<E>
    A basic implementation of a disjoint-set data structure for maintaining a collection of disjoint dynamic sets.
    EZIterator<E>
    An abstract class meant to make the implementation of iterators easier.
    EZIteratorWithNull<E>
    An abstract class meant to make the implementation of iterators easier.
    FilterIterator<E>
    An iterator ranging over a base iterator's range but including only those elements satisfying a condition.
    FirstNIterator<T>
    Iterator ranging over the n first elements in the range of another iterator.
    FunctionIterator<F,T>
    Iterator ranging over the results of an unary function applied to the elements of the range of a base iterator.
    GeometricSeriesIterator
    Implements an iterator going over a geometric series.
    HashMapRandomAccessTree
    An implementation of RandomAccessTree with HashMaps.
    HasNext<T>
    A Predicate that tests if a given iterator when applied hasNext().
    ImmutableStackedLinkedList<E>
    An implementation of an immutable List sharing elements with a pre-existing given list.
    InPlaceSubKTuplesIterator<E>
    An iterator over sub-tuples of k integers from 0 to n - 1, using the same collection instance to store all sub-tuples.
    InPlaceSubsetsOfKIterator<E>
    An iterator over subsets of k integers from 0 to n - 1, using the same collection instance to store all subsets.
    IntegerArithmeticSeriesIterator
    Implements an iterator going over an arithmetic series.
    IntegerGeometricSeriesIterator
    A geometric series rounded to the next integer.
    IntegerIterator
    An iterator over a given integer interval [start, end[ (that is, with inclusive start and exclusive end) with a specified increment over the interval.
    LazyIteratorAdapter<F,T>  
    LexicographicComparator<T>
    A comparator lexicographically composed by a list of comparators.
    LexicographicComparison<T extends java.lang.Comparable>
    A generic implementation of lexicographical comparison using iterators.
    ManyToManyRelation<A,B>
    Represents a many-to-many relation with amortized constant-time search for the tuples of a given element.
    MapWrapper<K,V>
    A Map that wraps a given map.
    NestedIterator<E>
    An iterator that does not range over its elements, but over ranges of sub-iterators computed from its elements.
    NIterator<E>

    A lazy iterator adapter that runs up to a given number of iterations.
    NonDeterministicIterator<E>
    An abstract iterator ranging over elements on the leaves of a virtual tree.
    PairIterator<T1,T2>
    A PairIterator is constructed on two iterators, and iterates over pairs of their next elements until one of them runs out of elements.
    PairOfElementsInListIterator<E>
    An iterator over pairs of distinct elements in an List, such that each pair's first element occurs before the second in the list.
    PermutationIterator<E>
    An iterator over permutations of a given ArrayList.
    PredicateIterator<E>
    Iterates over range of base iterator, only letting pass elements satisfying a predicate.
    StackedHashMap<K,V>
    An implementation of AbstractStackedMap using HashMap and HashSet.
    StackedLinkedList<E>
    An implementation of List sharing elements with a pre-existing given list.
    StackedTreeMap<K,V>

    StringIterator
    An iterator over the characters of a given string.
    SubKTuplesIterator<E>
    An iterator over k-tuples of a given ArrayList.
    SubRangeIterator<T>
    An iterator over a sub-range of a base iterator, from the first -th to the (last-1)-th element.
    SubsetsOfKIterator<E>
    An iterator over subsets of k elements of a given ArrayList.
    ToStringComparator<T>
    A comparator returning the same as the comparison of the string representations of objects.
